This paper is about an enhanced dropout technique for deep neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and specifically in deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the paper focuses on image classification tasks. The paper also discusses the impact of the technique on the generalization of the network, which is related to the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of convolution layers, which is a common technique in natural language processing, leading to the possibility of the paper being relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
